{
  "stem": "10588.1",
  "chunk_idx": 12,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 44,
      "text": "And she used it to cook her potatoes.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 45,
      "text": "And in the book, the story said that if he had a name, even if the 100 years, maybe somebody would say that 'Here lays Bontsha.' In this way, he vanished, like he would never live, even like a grain of sand.",
      "word_count": 42
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 46,
      "text": "And then, when he came to the next world, he was-- everybody knew-- they treated him well.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 47,
      "text": "And they said, 'In the other world where you came from, there is no justice.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 48,
      "text": "But in this world is justice.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 49,
      "text": "And anything you want is yours.'",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And he couldn't believe.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Why would somebody be so nice here if nobody was nice there?",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And he said, '[NON-ENGLISH]?",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Really?",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Really?' In Yiddish, [NON-ENGLISH] is 'really.' And he said, 'Yes.' So after giving it a lot of thought, he said, 'Well, in that case, what I would wish, your excellency, is every morning for breakfast a hot roll with butter.'",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And when I was in Auschwitz, I was thinking, the biggest millionaire couldn't have a roll, a hot roll with butter.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "To have some bread, I understood at that time, the story.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I also understood that six million have no graves and no markers, just like Bontsha [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And I understood something much deeper than that.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "To me, even though my mother didn't say this, because when she-- but I felt-- we would have had a homeland.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "We wouldn't be an orphan like Bontsha [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Nobody would keep us chasing from place to place, and even if we lived for so many years.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "My family, on my mother's side, came to Poland in the 1600 century from Germany.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And four generations were still alive, you know, when they came in.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And when we left there-- and I never will remember a remark that somebody made.",
      "word_count": 15
    }
  ],
